A Boolean Type
C++ contains a type named bool
Type bool has two symbolic constants
true
false
Boolean operators
The andoperator is &&
The oroperator is ||
The notoperator is !
Warning
&and |are also operators so be careful what you type
A Boolean Type
Example logical expressions
bool P = true;
bool Q = false;
bool R = true;bool S = (P && Q);bool T = ((!Q) || R);bool U = !(R && (!Q));

